\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  pulchellum} (Loisel.) Thell., {\i Fl. Adv. Montpellier} 186 (1912) ({\i P. pulchellum} Loisel.): Flowers solitary or in pairs, forming lax spikes throughout the inflorescence. Nut dull or scarcely glossy. 2n = 20.{\i  Mediterranean region, mainly in the east}.
