\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. P. albanicum} Jáv., {\i Bot. Közl. }{\b 19:}18 (1920). Annual. Stems 10-50 cm, diffusely branched from the base, erect. Leaves lanceolate to linear-lanceolate, acute, with a single vein, caducous. Flowers solitary or paired, rarely in clusters of 3; bracts inconspicuous, only the lowermost exceeding the flowers. Perianth 1·3-2 mm; segments longer than the tube, green with white or pink margins, connivent. Nut 1·5-2 mm, dark brown, rather glossy, distinctly exceeding the perianth. {\i Serpentine soils. • W. part of Balkan peninsula; local.} Al Gr Ju.
\par

