\pard\f0\fs28 Plants from the Black Sea and N. Aegean coasts, which have been called {\i P. mesembricum} Chrtek, {\i Preslia }{\b 32:} 367 (1960), appear to be annual, with greyish-green or silvery leaves, ochreae with 6-8 veins, and white margins to the perianth. The nut is similar to that of subsp. ({\b b}), but in some cultivated specimens can approach that of subsp. ({\b a}). In spite of the geographical disjunction there are no constant differences between this and subsp. ({\b b}).
